<TITLE> BCB floats tender for national team's sponsorship rights </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)The Bangladesh Cricket Board has invited bids from local and international parties for the sponsorship rights of the national team for the next two years. The tender schedule will be available from October 11 to November 4, according to an advertisement published Tuesday on tigercricket.com, BCB's official website. BCB expects to open the tenders at the Dhaka Sheraton Hotel on November 5 between 11:00am to 1:00pm. In this regard, a floor price will be announced on October 29 at BCB's management office in Navana Tower, Gulshan. The sponsorship rights exclude beverages, branded bottled drinking water, internet service providers and sportswear manufacturers, said the advertisement. Leading mobile phone operator Grameen Phone has sponsored the national team for the last three years. Its contract with BCB ended in July, though Grammen Phone extended its contract to cover the Bangladesh tour of Sri Lanka in June-July. AB Bank sponsored the Bangladesh team during the ICC Twenty20 World Cup in September. 
